Accessibility test digest

Synopsis

Page: The University of Texas MD Anderson Cancer Center (100%)

URL: https://www.mdanderson.org/

Score: 2597

Tested by: Testaro, procedure tp15

Scored by: Testilo, procedure sp15c

Digested by: Testilo, procedure dp15a

Introduction

The Testaro application used its tp15 testing procedure to test the accessibility (barrier-free design and coding) of the The University of Texas MD Anderson Cancer Center (100%) web page at https://www.mdanderson.org/ on 2022/08/13. The procedure performed 1230 tests. Of these, 24 are custom tests defined by Testaro, and the others belong to these seven other packages (programs that perform collections of tests):

  • Alfa by Siteimprove
  • Axe-core by Deque
  • Continuum by Level Access
  • HTML CodeSniffer by Squiz Labs
  • Equal Access by IBM
  • Nu Html Checker
  • Tenon by Level Access
  • WAVE by WebAIM

Testaro produced a report enumerating the test results.

Testilo processed the report and used the sp15c scoring procedure to compute partial and total scores for the page. The total score is 2597 (where 0 is the best possible score). The scored report is appended below.

Finally, Testilo used procedure dp15a to produce this digest, briefly explaining how sp15c computed the scores.

Issue summary

Special issues

log: Score 1103. This is based on the amount of browser error logging and miscellaneous logging during the tests.

preventions: Score 100. This is based on tests that the page did not allow to be run. That impedes accessibility progress and risks interfering with tools that users with disabilities need.

Classified issues

linkIndication: Score 243. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package testaro, test linkUl, score 241 (Non-underlined adjacent links)

visibleLabelNotName: Score 161. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r14, score 15 (Visible label is not in the accessible name)
  • Package axe, test label-content-name-mismatch, score 11 (Element visible text is not part of its accessible name)
  • Package htmlcs, test w:AA.2_5_3.F96, score 19 (Visible label is not in the accessible name)
  • Package ibm, test WCAG21_Label_Accessible, score 141 (Accessible name does not match or contain the visible label text)

hoverSurprise: Score 117. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package testaro, test hover, score 115 (Content changes caused by hovering)

linkForcesNewWindow: Score 89. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package tenon, test 218, score 87 (Link opens in a new window without user control)

leadingClipsText: Score 86. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package tenon, test 144, score 84 (Line height is insufficent to properly display the computed font size)

duplicateID: Score 53. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r3, score 30 (Element id attribute value is not unique)
  • Package axe, test duplicate-id-active, score 2 (id attribute value of the active element is not unique)
  • Package axe, test duplicate-id, score 2 (id attribute value is not unique)
  • Package continuum, test 94, score 21 (Elements contains an id attribute set to a value that is not unique in the DOM)
  • Package htmlcs, test e:AA.4_1_1.F77, score 12 (Duplicate id attribute value)
  • Package ibm, test RPT_Elem_UniqueId, score 15 (Element id attribute value is not unique within the document)
  • Package nuVal, test ^Duplicate ID .+$|^The first occurrence of ID .* was here.*$, score 1 (Duplicate id)

noLeading: Score 44. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r73, score 42 (Paragraph of text has insufficient line height)

contrastAA: Score 34. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r69, score 8 (Text outside widget has subminimum contrast)
  • Package axe, test color-contrast, score 20 (Element has insufficient color contrast)
  • Package htmlcs, test e:AA.1_4_3.G18.Fail, score 12 (Contrast between the text and its background is less than 4.5:1)
  • Package wave, test c:contrast, score 9 (Very low contrast)

iframeTitleBad: Score 33. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r13, score 16 (iframe has no accessible name)
  • Package axe, test frame-title, score 3 (Frame has no accessible name)
  • Package continuum, test 228, score 4 (iframe has no mechanism that allows an accessible name to be calculated)
  • Package htmlcs, test e:AA.2_4_1.H64.1, score 20 (iframe element has no non-empty title attribute)
  • Package ibm, test WCAG20_Frame_HasTitle, score 4 (Inline frame has an empty or nonunique title attribute)

contrastAAA: Score 33. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r66, score 10 (Text contrast less than AAA requires)
  • Package axe, test color-contrast-enhanced, score 24 (Element has insufficient color contrast (Level AAA))
  • Package tenon, test 95, score 8 (Element has insufficient color contrast (Level AAA))

imageNoText: Score 30. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r2, score 28 (Image has no accessible name)

linkTextsSame: Score 30. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package tenon, test 98, score 28 (Links have the same text but different destinations)

targetSize: Score 29. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package tenon, test 152, score 27 (Actionable element is smaller than the minimum required size)

controlNoText: Score 28. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package htmlcs, test e:AA.1_3_1.F68, score 12 (Form control has no label)
  • Package ibm, test WCAG20_Input_ExplicitLabel, score 16 (Form control has no associated label)
  • Package wave, test e:label_missing, score 12 (form element has no label)

attributeBad: Score 22. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package nuVal, test ^Bad value .* for attribute .+ on element .+$, score 8 (attribute on this element has an invalid value)
  • Package nuVal, test ^Attribute .+ not allowed on element .+ at this point.*$, score 4 (attribute not allowed on this element)
  • Package nuVal, test ^Attribute .+ is only allowed when .+$, score 8 (Attribute is invalid here)

fontSmall: Score 21. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package wave, test a:text_small, score 2 (Text is very small)
  • Package tenon, test 134, score 18 (Text is very small)

fontSizeAbsolute: Score 18. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r74, score 16 (Paragraph text has an absolute font size)

ariaBadAttribute: Score 18. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package axe, test aria-allowed-attr, score 16 (ARIA attribute is invalid for the role of its element)

inputNoText: Score 18. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package axe, test aria-input-field-name, score 9 (ARIA input field has no accessible name)
  • Package htmlcs, test e:AA.4_1_2.H91.InputText.Name, score 12 (Text input has no accessible name)

headingEmpty: Score 17. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r64, score 6 (Heading has no non-empty accessible name)
  • Package axe, test empty-heading, score 2 (Heading empty)
  • Package htmlcs, test e:AA.1_3_1.H42.2, score 6 (Heading empty)
  • Package ibm, test RPT_Header_HasContent, score 6 (Heading element provides no descriptive text)
  • Package nuVal, test Empty heading., score 2 (Empty heading)
  • Package wave, test e:heading_empty, score 6 (Empty heading)

focusableOperable: Score 15. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package testaro, test focOp, score 13 (Operable elements that cannot be Tab-focused and vice versa)

roleBad: Score 15. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package testaro, test role, score 9 (Nonexistent or implicit-overriding role)
  • Package ibm, test element_tabbable_role_valid, score 9 (Tabbable element has a non-widget role)

childMissing: Score 15. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r68, score 12 (Element does not own an element required by its semantic role)
  • Package axe, test aria-required-children, score 3 (ARIA role does not contain a required child)

formFieldNoText: Score 14. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r8, score 12 (Form field has no accessible name)

inconsistentStyles: Score 12. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package testaro, test styleDiff, score 10 (Heading, link, and button style inconsistencies)

typeRedundant: Score 12. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package nuVal, test The type attribute is unnecessary for JavaScript resources., score 9 (type attribute is unnecessary for a JavaScript resource)
  • Package nuVal, test The type attribute for the style element is not needed and should be omitted., score 1 (type attribute is unnecessary for a style element)

zIndexNotZero: Score 11. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package testaro, test zIndex, score 9 (Layering with nondefault z-index values)

inputOnlyPlaceholder: Score 11. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package continuum, test 863, score 9 (input has an accessible name that depends on a placeholder)

linkNoText: Score 11. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package htmlcs, test e:AA.4_1_2.H91.A.NoContent, score 4 (Link has an href attribute but no text)
  • Package ibm, test WCAG20_A_HasText, score 4 (Hyperlink has no text description)
  • Package wave, test e:link_empty, score 4 (Link contains no text)
  • Package tenon, test 57, score 4 (Link has no text inside it)

searchConfusion: Score 11. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package ibm, test Rpt_Aria_MultipleSearchLandmarks, score 9 (Element with a search role has no unique purpose label among the search-role elements)

focusIndication: Score 10. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package testaro, test focInd, score 7 (Focused element displaying no or nostandard focus indicator)
  • Package alfa, test r65, score 3 (Element in sequential focus order has no visible focus)

overflowHidden: Score 10. Issues reported by tests in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r83, score 8 (Overflow is hidden or clipped if the text is enlarged)
